no]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''17''' ||[[Steve Corica]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''22''' ||[[Mile Sterjovski]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''18'''||[[Paul Agostino]] || {{subon|62}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''21'''||[[John Aloisi]] || {{subon|81}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|[[Frank Farina]]\n|}\n|}\n{| width=100% style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''OFFICIALS'''\n*Assistant referees:\n**[[Ahmed Yaqqob Mohamed]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n**[[Ali Abdulla Makhlouf]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n*Fourth official: [[Musallam Al Bloushi]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''MATCH RULES'''\n*90 minutes\n*30 minutes of [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra-time]] if necessary\n*Penalty shoot-out if scores still level:\n*3 (of 7) [[Substitute (football)|substitutions]] permitted\n|}\n\n== Aftermath ==\nUruguay qualified for the 2002 FIFA World Cup Finals in [[South Korea]] and [[Japan]], and were drawn into Group A with [[1998 FIFA World Cup|defending champions]] [[France national football team|France]], [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] and debutants [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].  After losing 2\u20131 to Denmark in their opening match, Uruguay drew France 0\u20130 and in the final match they also drew 3\u20133 to Senegal despite being 3\u20130 down, finishing third in the group on two points.\n\nAustralia played in the [[2002 OFC Nations Cup]] qualified automatically. The Socceroos were drawn into a group with [[Vanuatu national football team|Vanuatu]], [[Fiji national football team|Fiji]] and [[New Caledonia national football team|New Caledonia]] and won 2\u20130, 11\u20130 and 8\u20130 respectively, and topped the group, proceeding to the semi-final stage. Against [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]], a goal from [[Damian Mori]] in extra time secured a 2\u20131 win and a place in the final against [[New Zealand national football team|New Zealand]]. Australia lost 1\u20130, leaving the side as runners-up and New Zealand qualifying for the [[2003 FIFA Confederations Cup]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2002 FIFA World Cup qualification}}\n{{Australia national football team matches}}\n{{Uruguay national football team matches}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2002 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL-OFC play-off)}}\n[[Category:2001 in Australian soccer|FIFA]]\n[[Category:2002 FIFA World Cup qualification|Play-off CONMEBOL-OFC]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup qualification inter-confederation play-offs]]\n[[Category:Australia national soccer team matches]]\n[[Category:Uruguay national football team matches]]\n[[Category:2001 in Uruguayan football|World]]\n[[Category:Uruguay at the 2002 FIFA World Cup|qual]]\n[[Category:November 2001 sports events in Oceania]]\n[[Category:November 2001 sports events in South America]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Melbourne]]\n[[Category:Sports competitions in Montevideo]]\n[[Category:2000s in Melbourne]]\n[[Category:2000s in Montevideo]]\n[[Category:International association football competitions hosted by Australia]]\n[[Category:International association football competitions hosted by Uruguay]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football match\n| title                   = 2002 FIFA World Cup qualification <br> ([[CONMEBOL]]\u2013[[Oceania Football Confederation|OFC]] play-off)\n| image                   = \n| event                   = [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification]]\n| team1                   = [[Australia national association football team|Australia]]\n| team1association        = {{flagicon|Australia|size=30px}}\n| team1score              = 1\n| team2                   = [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]]\n| team2association        = {{flagicon|Uruguay|size=30px}}\n| team2score              = 3\n| details                 = Uruguay won 3\u20131 on aggregate\n| firstleg                = First leg\n| team1score1             = 1\n| team2score1             = 0\n| details1              