], and the fifth-placed team from the [[2002 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL)|South American qualifying tournament]], [[Uruguay national football team|Uruguay]]. The games were played on 20 November and 25 November 2001 in [[Melbourne]] and [[Montevideo]] respectively. Australia was hoping to play in the FIFA World Cup for the first time since [[1974 FIFA World Cup|1974]] and Uruguay since [[1990 FIFA World Cup|1990]].\n\n==Background==\n{|  style=\"width:100%; text-align:center;\"\n|-  style=\"vertical-align:top; background:#9cf;\"\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|Uruguay\n!Round\n!colspan=2 style=\"width:1*\"|Australia\n|-\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:175px;\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GF | Goals for}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GA | Goals against}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| GD | Goal difference}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pts | Points}}\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|Argentina}}\n|18||13||4||1||42||15||27||'''43'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|Ecuador}}\n|18||9||4||5||23||20||3||'''31'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|Brazil}}\n|18||9||3||6||31||17||14||'''30'''\n|- style=\"background:#ccffcc;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|Paraguay}}\n|18||9||3||6||29||23||6||'''30'''\n|- style=\"background:#ffebad;\"\n|style=\"text-align:left;\"|{{fb|Uruguay}}\n|18||7||6||5||19||13||6||'''27'''\n|-\n|}\n| style=\"background:#c1e0ff;\"|Final standings\n| colspan=\"2\" align=\"center\"|\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:175px;\"|Team\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| Pld | Played}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| W | Won}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| D | Drawn}}\n!width=\"20\"|{{Tooltip| L | Lost}}\n!w