on]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])\n|-\n|MF ||'''8''' ||[[Josip Skoko]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''11'''||[[Stan Lazaridis]] || ||{{suboff|45}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''9''' ||[[Mark Viduka]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''10'''||[[Harry Kewell]]\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Substitutions:'''\n|-\n|GK ||'''12'''||[[\u017deljko Kalac]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''6''' ||[[Tony Popovic]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''16'''||[[Steve Horvat]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''13'''||[[Mark Bresciano]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''17'''||[[Steve Corica]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''18'''||[[Paul Agostino]] || ||{{subon|45}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''21'''||[[John Aloisi]]\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|[[Frank Farina]]\n|}\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=center\n|-\n!width=\"25\"| !!width=\"25\"|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1''' ||[[Fabi\u00e1n Carini]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''2''' ||[[Washington Tais]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''3''' ||[[Alejandro Lembo]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''4''' ||[[Paolo Montero]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])\n|-\n|DF ||'''6''' ||[[Dar\u00edo Rodr\u00edguez]] || || {{yel|34}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''8''' ||[[Gonzalo de los Santos]] || || {{sent off|0|68}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''5''' ||[[Pablo Gabriel Garc\u00eda]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''7''' ||[[Gianni Guigou]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''20'''||[[\u00c1lvaro Recoba]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''19'''||[[Javier Chevant\u00f3n]] || ||{{suboff|77}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''11''' ||[[Federico Magallanes]] || ||{{suboff|71}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Substitutions:'''\n|-\n|GK ||'''12'''||[[Gustavo Mun\u00faa]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''14'''||[[Joe Bizera]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''10'''||[[Nicol\u00e1s Olivera]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''16'''||[[Guillermo Giacomazzi]] || ||{{subon|71}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''9''' ||[[Diego Alonso]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''15'''||[[Mario Regueiro]] || ||{{subon|77}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''18'''||[[Richard Morales]]\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|[[V\u00edctor P\u00faa]]\n|}\n|}\n{| width=100% style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''OFFICIALS'''\n*Assistant referees:\n**[[Marco Ivaldi]] ([[Italian Football Federation|Italy]])\n**[[Aniello Di Mauro]] ([[Italian Football Federation|Italy]])\n*Fourth official: [[Cosimo Bolognino]] ([[Italian Football Federation|Italy]])\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''MATCH RULES'''\n*90 minutes\n*3 (of 7) [[Substitute (association football)|substitutions]] permitted\n|}\n\n===Second leg===\n{{football box\n| date         = 25 November 2001\n| event        = \n| round        = \n| time         = 16:00 [[UTC\u221203:00|UTC\u22123]]\n| team1        = {{fb-rt|Uruguay}}\n| score        = 3\u20130\n| aet          = \n| report       = [https://www.fifa.com/worldcup/archive/edition=4395/preliminaries/preliminary=8024/matches/match=24860/report.html (Report)]\n| team2        = {{fb|Australia}}\n| goals1       = [[Dar\u00edo Silva|Silva]] {{goal|14}} <br> [[Richard Morales|Morales]] {{goal|70||90}}\n| goals2       = \n| stadium      = [[Estadio Centenario]], [[Montevideo]]\n| attendance   = 62,000\n| referee      = [[Ali Bujsaim]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n}}\n\n{| width=\"100%\"\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\"\n|-\n!width=\"25\"| !!width=\"25\"|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1''' ||[[Fabi\u00e1n Carini]] || {{yel|90+3}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''2'''||[[Washington Tais]] || {{yel|85}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''3''' ||[[Alejandro Lembo]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''4''' ||[[Paolo Montero]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])\n|-\n|DF ||'''6''' ||[[Dar\u00edo Rodr\u00edguez]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''5''' ||[[Pablo Gabriel Garc\u00eda]] || {{yel|66}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''7''' ||[[Gianni Guigou]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''10'''||[[Mario Regueiro]] || {{yel|10}} || {{suboff|64}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''20'''||[[\u00c1lvaro Recoba]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''9''' ||[[Dar\u00edo Silva]] || {{yel|81}} || {{suboff|81}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''11'''||[[Federico Magallanes]] || {{suboff|65}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Substitutions:'''\n|-\n|GK ||'''12'''||[[Gustavo Mun\u00faa]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''14'''||[[Gonzalo Sorondo]] || {{subon|81}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''8''' ||[[Gonzalo de los Santos]] || {{yel|80}} || {{subon|64}}\n|-\n|MF ||'''15'''||[[Guillermo Giacomazzi]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''16'''||[[Nicol\u00e1s Olivera]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''18''' ||[[Richard Morales]] || {{yel|70}} || {{subon|65}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''19''' ||[[Diego Alonso]]\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|[[V\u00edctor P\u00faa]]\n|}\n|valign=\"top\" width=\"50%\"|\n{| style=\"font-size: 90%\" cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" align=center\n|-\n!width=\"25\"| !!width=\"25\"|\n|-\n|GK ||'''1''' ||[[Mark Schwarzer]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''2''' ||[[Kevin Muscat]] || {{yel|32}} || {{suboff|62}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''14'''||[[Shaun Murphy (footballer)|Shaun Murphy]] || {{suboff|81}}\n|-\n|DF ||'''3''' ||[[Craig Moore]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''5''' ||[[Tony Vidmar]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''7''' ||[[Brett Emerton]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''4''' ||[[Paul Okon]] ([[Captain (association football)|c]])\n|-\n|MF ||'''8''' ||[[Josip Skoko]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''11'''||[[Stan Lazaridis]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''9''' ||[[Mark Viduka]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''10'''||[[Harry Kewell]] || {{suboff|71}}\n |-\n|colspan=3|'''Substitutions:'''\n|-\n|GK ||'''12'''||[[\u017deljko Kalac]]\n|-\n|DF ||'''16'''||[[Steve Horvat]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''13'''||[[Mark Bresciano]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''17''' ||[[Steve Corica]]\n|-\n|MF ||'''22''' ||[[Mile Sterjovski]]\n|-\n|FW ||'''18'''||[[Paul Agostino]] || {{subon|62}}\n|-\n|FW ||'''21'''||[[John Aloisi]] || {{subon|81}}\n|-\n|colspan=3|'''Manager:'''\n|-\n|colspan=\"4\"|[[Frank Farina]]\n|}\n|}\n{| width=100% style=\"font-size: 90%\"\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''OFFICIALS'''\n*Assistant referees:\n**[[Ahmed Yaqqob Mohamed]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n**[[Ali Abdulla Makhlouf]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n*Fourth official: [[Musallam Al Bloushi]] ([[United Arab Emirates Football Association|UAE]])\n| width=50% valign=top|\n'''MATCH RULES'''\n*90 minutes\n*30 minutes of [[Overtime (sports)#Association football|extra-time]] if necessary\n*Penalty shoot-out if scores still level:\n*3 (of 7) [[Substitute (football)|substitutions]] permitted\n|}\n\n== Aftermath ==\nUruguay qualified for the 2002 FIFA World Cup Finals in [[South Korea]] and [[Japan]], and were drawn into Group A with [[1998 FIFA World Cup|defending champions]] [[France national football team|France]], [[Denmark national football team|Denmark]] and debutants [[Senegal national football team|Senegal]].  After losing 2\u20131 to Denmark in their opening match, Uruguay drew France 0\u20130 and in the final match they also drew 3\u20133 to Senegal despite being 3\u20130 down, finishing third in the group on two points.\n\nAustralia played in the [[2002 OFC Nations Cup]] qualified automatically. The Socceroos were drawn into a group with [[Vanuatu national football team|Vanuatu]], [[Fiji national football team|Fiji]] and [[New Caledonia national football team|New Caledonia]] and won 2\u20130, 11\u20130 and 8\u20130 respectively, and topped the group, proceeding to the semi-final stage. Against [[Tahiti national football team|Tahiti]], a goal from [[Damian Mori]] in extra time secured a 2\u20131 win and a place in the final against [[New Zealand national football team|New Zealand]]. Australia lost 1\u20130, leaving the side with the silver medal and New Zealand qualifying for the [[2003 FIFA Confederations Cup]].\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{2002 FIFA World Cup qualification}}\n{{Australia national football team matches}}\n{{Uruguay national football team matches}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:2002 FIFA World Cup qualification (CONMEBOL-OFC play-off)}}\n[[Category:2001 in Australian soccer|FIFA]]\n[[Category:2002 FIFA World Cup qualification|Play-off CONMEBOL-OFC]]\n[[Category:FIFA World Cup qualification inter-confederation play-offs]]\n[[Category:Australia national soccer team matches]]\n[[Category:Uruguay national football team matches]]\n[[Category:2001 in Uruguayan football|World]]\n[[Category:Uruguay at the 2002 FIFA World Cup|qual]]\n[[Category:November 2001 sports events in Oceania]]\n[[Category:November 2001 sports events in South America]]\n[[Catego